@ad1992 the reason for using `createElement` is that React complains if the `children` don't have the `key` prop.

`<>{[child1, child2]}</>` is translated to `createElement(React.Fragment, { children: [child1, child2] })` and if `child1` or `child2` don't have `key` prop, React will complain.

`<>{child1}{child2}</>` is translated to `createElement(React.Fragment, {}, child1, child2)` (which is what we want to do).

