`1266-1299`: **Inline IIFE UI incurs re-render cost & leaks style constants**

Embedding an immediately-invoked function expression inside JSX recreates the floating panel on every parent render, preventing React diffing optimisations and making future maintenance harder.

Refactor into a memoised component:

```diff
-{excalidrawAPI && (() => {
-  …logic…
-})()}
+{excalidrawAPI && (
+  <RabbitSearchPanel key={excalidrawAPI.getAppState().editingElement?.id}
+                     excalidrawAPI={excalidrawAPI} />
+)}
```
Separating logic:
```tsx
const RabbitSearchPanel: React.FC<{excalidrawAPI: ExcalidrawImperativeAPI}> = ({excalidrawAPI}) => {
  …same math, return null/JSX…
};
```
Benefits: clearer intent, no per-render allocation, easier to unit-test.

